article.headline: Arkansas 83, Alabama 68
article.story:
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- Sarah Pfeifer's 21 points paced
Arkansas to an 83-68 Southeastern Conference victory Thursday night
over Alabama.

The win by Arkansas (14-8, 3-7 SEC) came one game after the Lady
Razorbacks shot a school-record worst-ever percentage of 23.5 at
Auburn.

"Sarah had a great game, but it was a total team effort,"
Arkansas coach Susie Gardner said. "We had people diving on the
floor, we had more focus on defense, and obviously we hit our
shots."

Arkansas hit its first seven shots from the field and two free
throws on the way to a 61.5 shooting percentage in the first half
against Alabama (13-9, 4-5). Arkansas led 50-33 at the half.

Kristin Peoples added 15 points for Arkansas, Rochelle Vaughn
came off the bench for 14 points and Danielle Allen scored 11.

Natasha Gamble led the Tide with 16 points, while Monique Bivins
had 13 and Navonda Moore scored 10.
